description: BRIGHTEST DAY shines on as the mystery of the White Lantern piques the curiosity of Hector Hammond. The bizarre telekinetic escapes his prison cell and sets his sights on one being â€“ Larfleeze! Plus, Hal Jordan begins unlocking the secret behind who took Parallax during BLACKEST NIGHT!
name: The New Guardians, Chapter 4

description: The fifth installment in Conan: The Frazetta Cover Series features both Frank Frazetta's tense, dramatic Man-Ape painting and an adaptation of Robert E. Howard's "Rogues in the House"-as interpreted by Timothy Truman, artists Cary Nord and TomÃ¡s Giorello, and colorist Richard Isanove. A longtime Howard favorite, this seminal Conan story first appeared in Weird Tales in 1934, and Frazetta's Man-Ape piece is one of his few Conan paintings to make a direct reference to one of Howard's works. Our favorite barbarian has been living as a thief for some time, and his crimes are catching up with him. Becoming enmeshed in the plans of a treacherous nobleman and a dark priest, Conan finds himself making some strange allies in order to free himself from the labyrinthine, booby-trapped halls in the Red Priest's stronghold. Stalked by a mysterious, hulking horror that's grown out of control, Conan and the nobleman make a wary alliance with the Red Priest himself!
name: Rogues in the House

description: The first of a two-part story featuring the return of Nathaniel Richards. Follow us as he jumps through time back to the college years of Reed, Ben and Victor Von Doom and recruits them for an impossible mission in the future.
name: When Everything's Lost, The Battle is Won...

description: Whoever said "War is Hell" didn't know the half of it. The Colonial Marines and their Predator allies look to take the fight to the enemy Predators and the Alien horde they control -- but the daunting numbers of the bug swarm may be more than human and hunter can overcome. Their last hope may lie in the synthetic hands of the android David Sereda, who discovers the enemy's bug hatchery and a secret that may stem the deadly Alien tide -- if he can survive long enough to tell the tale! Featuring the creative dream team of original AvP writer Randy Stradley, superstar penciller Rick Leonardi, inker Mark Pennington, colorist Wes Dzioba, and stunning cover artist Raymond Swanland, Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War ties together story threads introduced in the 1989 AvP series and new Aliens and Predator storylines, setting the stage for the most epic AvP brawl ever imagined.

volume.name: Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War

description: A cold-war nightmare is about to erupt on a ship carrying ancient relics protected by the dead. Written by Mike Mignola and John Arcudi, and featuring the chilling artwork of Peter Snejbjerg (B.P.R.D.: War on Frogs, Starman), The Abyssal Plain explores another early Abe solo adventure, in the spirit of Abe Sapien: The Drowning and Abe Sapien: The Haunted Boy.

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: When Buzzard enters a mysterious village plagued by an inhuman race of people-snatching savages, he's thrust into confrontation with the beasts and saves a young boy from harm. The grateful villagers invite him into their homes, and suspect they know the nature of his true identity-believing him their savior from a great, evil deity buried in the depths of the forest. Award-winning comics creator Eric Powell explores the twisted life of Buzzard, one of Powell's most beloved and mysterious characters from The Goon, in this highly anticipated three-issue miniseries.
name: Billy The Kid's Old Timey Oddities & The Pit Of Horrors, Part Two Of Three

description: BRIGHTEST DAY burns on as Cyborg-Superman returns! You won't believe how far he'll go to secure his sinister new secret agenda. Plus, Green Lantern Ganthet has made a clandestine deal with Atrocitus. What is it and why might it spell doom for the Green Lantern Corps? The Emerald Warriors might have survived the BLACKEST NIGHT just in time for a great evil to rise!
name: Revolt of the Alpha-Lanterns, Part 3

description: The prelude to the smash series from Kevin Smith and Dynamite continues as the story before their appearance in the pages of KEVIN SMITH'S GREEN HORNET is finally told! At the hands of the Black Hornet, Kato is faced with an unimaginable loss! Will he find the strength to survive? Featuring another awesome line-up of covers from Benitez, Garza and Johnny D!

The original Captain Boomerang returns as BRIGHTEST DAY continues. Meanwhile, Barry must prove his innocence to the Renegades, cops from the 25th century. Discover what connection they have to the Rogues and what travesties have occurred in the future.

Captain Boomerang and the Flash discuss the Renegades. Boomerang causes a police helicopter to crash but the Flash saves the pilots. The Renegades want to arrest Boomerang too but he attacks them with his new weapons. Flash catches the weapons and lets them explode in safety to protect everyone.

Top thinks something is wrong about their mission and thinks Flash saving them means something. Heatstroke wants to stick to their rules and not interfer with the past. Top goes to talk to Flash and tells him that he will kill Iris in the future, so that he won't do it.

Iris finds something in the evidence that Barry took while Singh notices that the file is missing.

Top tells Barry that the Rogues plan an attack on him with a weapon they can't control. The Mirror Lords will take possession of Iris, turning her into the Mirror Mistress and Barry will have to kill her. Top tells him that he just has to attack the Rogues before they get a chance to get to him.

Heatstroke tells Commander Cold about Top breaking the law. Before they can do something, Captain Cold arrives with the dangerous weapon.
name: Case One: The Dastardly Death Of The Rogues Part Four

story_arc_credits.name: The Dastardly Death Of The Rogues

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Dastardly Death Of The Rogues

description: In this start to a new storyline, the Page Sisters finally find a new purpose in life: restoring the Great Library. And the one place you don't want to be is between them and one of the books they want. Meanwhile, Jack Frost has just set upon the greatest quest in a long and distinguished career of great quests, all of which have been great...and questy. Plus, Jack's still a dragon. That ain't gonna change, folks.
name: Hot Librarians! The First Ingredient in the Ultimate Jack of Fables Story!

story_arc_credits.name: The Ultimate Jack of Fables Story

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Ultimate Jack of Fables Story

description: 'PUNISHMENT': PART 2 OF 4 A DARK WOLVERINE/FRANKEN-CASTLE CROSSOVER! The rematch you begged for: Punisher vs Daken! A few months ago, Wolverine's son hunted down Frank Castle at the behest of a vengeance-seeking Norman Osborn and sliced him to ribbons. But Frank's feeling better now, and he's ready for round two - as Franken-Castle! Everything you ever wanted all in one comic - in the most brutal, down-in-the-dirt, blood-soaked, slugfest the law will allow per page -- guaranteed to kick you right in your damned face, in mighty Marvel fashion, naturally
name: Punishment (Part 2)

description: When Lex Luthor finally regained control of LexCorp, he thought he had everything he wanted. But in BLACKEST NIGHT, he briefly became an Orange Lantern and got a taste of true power. Now he'll do anything â€“ anything â€“ to get that power back. Buckle in for a greatest hits tour of the DCU's most wanted as Lex Luthor begins an epic quest for power, all brought to you by new ongoing writer Paul Cornell (Dr. Who, Captain Britain and MI-13) and artist Pete Woods (WORLD OF NEW KRYPTON), with covers by David Finch (BRIGHTEST DAY, Ultimatum)!
name: The Black Ring, Part Two

description: Mr. X has traveled near and far and faced some of the best fighters the world has to offer. Years of training and mastery of various martial arts have turned him into one of the deadliest men alive. He's even beaten Wolverine, becoming one of the most dangerous members of his rogue's gallery. So... has any of this prepared him for what happens when the Merc with a Mouth is contracted to kill him?
name: X Marks The Spot

description: Years in the Making! Thirteen mystical Artifacts, including the Witchblade, the Darkness and others, guide the fate of the Top Cow Universe. For centuries, it's been whispered that bringing together all 13 Artifacts would herald mankind's destruction. But a mysterious figure has been manipulating events, laying plans to put Armageddon into motion. The final phase begins here, with the abduction of Hope, the daughter of Sara Pezzini and Jackie Estacado. What ensues will remake the entirety of the Top Cow Universe, from the Witchblade and the Darkness, to the Angelus, Magdalena, and even Cyberforce. â€¢
name: "Artifacts" part 1 of 13; "Origin: Witchblade"

description: APOCALYPSE WAS RIGHT. In the wake of last issue's devastating climax, X-Factor has discovered that the ancient mutant's portents of doom were more than idle threats. With the Celestials' hour of judgment upon them, it's up to Xavier's original mutants to make the greatest sacrifice of all. It's a FOREVER farewell from X-Legend Louise Simonson!
name: Collateral Damage

description: What hides in the depths of the red planet? How does it link to the Shadow Empire lurking behind the scenes in America for nearly 150 years? And will our heroes be able to save one of their own? The Secret Avengers duo Ed Brubaker and Mike Deodato bring the action.
name: Secret Histories, Part 3

description:
Just as the girls begin working as a team, a new threat destroys everything! Can they reunite in time â€“ or will this be the end of the Sirens? Poison Ivy finds out about a mysterious plant alien known as the Alstairean. At her new position at Gotham City, S.T.A.R. Labs.

The origin of the Alstairean is given and the story is too much for Ivy to resist as she soon revitalizes the Alien. He is able to manipulate her and the two of them plan to take over the world starting with Gotham City. It is up to Harley Quinn and Catwoman to save her from the Alstairean but she may not want to be saved.

Also in this issue is a four page preview of the Green Lantern: Emerald Warriors series. The Preview is of book one of the series. DC Comics has done this a lot lately and the same preview is in several DC books that came out this month.
name: Strange Fruit, Part One

first_appearance_locations.name: Gotham City Shelter for Cats and Dogs

location_credits.name: Gotham City Shelter for Cats and Dogs

description: On the trail of Moses, his wife Sera, weary from the horror that has pervaded her life, stops to witness an Acholi wedding. Tradition and love beneath a sprawling blue sky... now she'll have to convince herself to turn her back on a beautiful world and follow Moses into the darkness.
name: Beautiful World, Chapter One

description: Spencer's got great hearing for a '60s ad exec. So great, in fact, that he can hear thoughts â€“ but not the kind of thoughts you want to hear. Spencer hears voices that want him to hurt others and even female voices offering lurid temptations. When Madame Xanadu suspects the influence of a malevolent spirit and intervenes, Spencer refuses. Can he resist the violent impulses â€“ or will he face a lifetime of heartache? Find out in part 2 of "Extra Sensory" featuring guest art from the talented Laurenn McCubbin (Rent Girls).
name: Extra-Sensory, Chapter 2: Dirty Little Mouth

description: Senses are shattering and pulses pounding as generations new and old experience this ultimate tale. THE GREEN HORNET STRIKES! Features the writing of acclaimed Lone Ranger scribe Brett Matthews, cover artist John Cassaday and interior artist Ariel Padilla! Issue #2 continues the excitement begun in our debut as this new Hornet makes his way through the underworld of Chicago and the tangled world above! Ask your local retailer for the incredible line-up of incentive covers to complete your collection! Â

The finale to Kevin Smith and Walt Flanagan's Batman tale! Thanks to Silver St. Cloud, Bruce is trying to learn how to trust people. But Batman is an integral part of who he is, so how can he really trust anyone? Batman even has a run-in with Catwoman because of his relationship with Silver. And when he decides to put all of his trust into someone, will he be rewarded...or punished? Don't miss this extra-sized finale to volume one of WIDENING GYRE!

And this is the issue that Batman admits he peed in his pants...seriously.
name: The Blood-Dimmed Tide Is Loosed

description: The four-part epic "BATMAN: IMPOSTERS" begins with this thirty-page adventure! A call to arms has gone out through Gotham City, and normal, everyday citizens are being drafted into a bizarre battle. Will they side with vigilante justice or join the cause of chaos and anarchy? Only The Dark Knight can rein in the terror created by the villain known only as The Imposter. But what is The Imposter's true motivation for this gang war â€” and what's hiding behind his rictus grin? Be here to find out!
name: Batman: Impostors, Part 1: "Laugh and the World Laughs With You"

description: Best-selling comics writer J. Michael Straczynski (THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD, Thor) smashes all your expectations of Wonder Woman by lauching an all-new era for the Amazon Princess! Spinning out of the mind-bending events of WONDER WOMAN #600, Diana must face the biggest mystery of all - who destroyed Paradise Island?
name: Past Imperfect, Present Tense

description: Now that the Ultimate Enemy has revealed his plan, the heroes of the Ultimate Universe search to discover their enemy's true identity before any more damage can be done. Join the Ultimate heroes on a chase that will take them all over the world and beyond! Superstar creator Brian Michael Bendis and artist sensation Rafa Sandoval continue to thrill in the next segment of the Enemy Trilogy!

This issues Fantomah-story isn`t made by fletcher Hanks. It`s by W.B.Hovious (a fake name), and in it, Fantomah is a woman with heightened senses and has the physical prowess of a typical Jungle hero. She also has a bit of magical abilities. No more flaming skulls and weird punishments, though. There`s still an effort to make stories with Hanks style.
This issues Fantomah-story isn`t made by fletcher Hanks. It`s by W.B.Hovious (a fake name), and in it, Fantomah is the same like she was in the previous issue.
Fantomah is the same as she was in issue 16.

Doc Savage and The Spirit have joined forces at last â€“ but can they beat the secrets behind the death of Doc's father out of the Blackhawks? The Batman just might be two steps ahead of them all! And in the jungles of South America, it's getting harder and harder for Rima to keep William Littlejohn alive as the forces of the Golden Tree close inâ€¦
name: First Wave - Book 3

description: In a flashback from the explosion a few issues earlier Captain Atom travels through time due to that explosion. While in regular time the Newly re-formed Justice League International makes plans to stop Maxwell Lord. Also, there is a Captain Atom Origin Story in the beginning of the issue.
name: Splitting The Atom

description: The Great Divide continues! Separated by two continents and personal differences, the two Outsiders teams are pushed to their limits. Black Lightning, Owl Man and newest member Freight Train take on the combined might of Chemomorpho while Geo-Force and his army invade a neighboring country - only to come face-to-face with that country's defender, The Olympian!
name: Elements Of Mass Destruction

description: It's the action-packed conclusion to "Tomorrow Dies Today"...and at the end of it only one Deathlok shall remain. As Logan and the greatest heroes of the Marvel U unite to confront him, the question is raised: is he friend or foe? Or maybe even both?
name: Tomorrow Dies Today, Conclusion

description: On Tirol, everyone is preparing for a visit from the Invid Regent, while back on Praxis, the stranded Sentinels are still trying to figure out a way to get off of the planet and Burak and Tesla have formed a partnership.
name: The Dance of Death

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Starring Spider-Man. On the trail of a fugitive Venom, Spider-Man runs across one of his even nastier foes, the savage Scorpion! This reader-friendly stand alone story features animated-style art.
name: The Name of the Game

description: On his home planet the Invid Regent is curious to know what news the clone he sent to Tiral has; on the SDF-3, a murder has occurred; and on Praxis, the Sentinels may have found a power source that will help them get off the planet.
name: The Hand at Work

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description:
A division among the crew of the SDF-3 may be occurring; Arla-Non, the mother of all Praxians confronts the Regiss on Haydon IV; and on Praxis, the Sentinels put together an escape plan.

Note: Inside back cover has a pinup of the Design-Your-Own-Robotech-Character Contest.
name: A Ship Divided

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Burak and Tesla deviate from the Sentinels's plan to escape from Praxis but Janice may be able to stop them and back on Praxis, the Sentinels have a new problem. Issue also has an interview about the Invid War: Aftermath Robotech saga.
name: When Worlds Implode!

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Rick Hunter and the Sentinels try to figure out what is going on in the caves of Praxis, Wolf and Saran manage to get on Tesla and Burak's ship but Janice has a surprise in store.
name: Into the Pit

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Dr. Lang finds his search and rescue attempts for the Hunters and the Sentinels thwarted. But he's not about to give up as he goes off on his own and Edwards and the Invid Regent's clone continue to negotiate.
name: Return of the Native

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Jonathan Wolf has made it back to the SDF-3 and tries to get a rescue operation going for everyone trapped on Praxis but he finds surprising opposition to such a plan. However, Dr. Lang has another plan and unfortunately so does Edwards.
name: Wild Card

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Jonathan Wolf, Janice, Burak and Tesla, with Dr. Lang's help, escape to the SDF-7 and take off to rescue the Sentinels.
name: Escape from Tirol

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Last apperence of Pat Parker (who by then dropped the War Nurse ID and gone blonde) and the Girl Commandos

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Wedding Special
Robotech II: The Sentinels - Wedding Special

description: the gore-fest continues as the re-animated killer Edgar Dill and his legion of flesh-eating treehuggers finally get their chance for revenge against the one who stopped the bloodshed some thirty years ago.

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - The Malcontent Uprisings

description: the slaughter fest reaches it's bloody climax as the resurrected serial killer Eddie Dill and his growing legion of flesh-hungry TreeHuggers move in for the final kill. Will sheriff Lundy and the surviving kids find some way to escape? or Will Eddie "clean" the girls and feed Lundy to his "angels"?

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - The Malcontent Uprisings
Robotech II: The Sentinels - The Malcontent Uprisings
